## Activity Observed

### User Account Creation

A new local user account was successfully created.

Observed User:

```text
AdminTest
```

Security Significance:

* Creation of unauthorized accounts may indicate persistence activity.
* New accounts should always be reviewed during incident investigations.

---

### Administrative Group Membership Change

The newly created account was added to the local Administrators group.

Security Significance:

* Grants elevated privileges.
* Increases attacker control over the system.
* Common post-compromise persistence technique.

---

## Investigation Findings

### Event Analysis

Wazuh successfully collected and displayed events related to:

* User account creation
* Local group membership modification
* Administrative privilege assignment

The activity was visible within the Wazuh dashboard and correlated with MITRE ATT&CK mappings.

